# Site Overview
# Shows how Copilot understands the structure and content of a SharePoint site.

[section: setup]

Navigate to the site and verify the Copilot FAB is visible before the demo.
If the chat pane is already open from a previous session, close it.

[navigate: https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]

[open-chat]

The chat pane should be open and showing "Hello" with prompt suggestions.
If it shows a previous conversation, clear it before proceeding.

[pause]

[section: demo]

[navigate: https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]

Welcome to Zach's Demo Site — a purpose-built SharePoint environment with a wide
variety of lists, libraries, pages, and content types. We use it to demonstrate
real Microsoft 365 Copilot capabilities in a controlled setting.

Take a moment to point out the left nav and the hero image.

[pause]

[open-chat]

The Copilot chat pane is now open. Notice it loaded in the sidebar — this is the
standard Copilot experience built into SharePoint. No plugins required.

[prompt: Tell me about this site]

[wait]

Copilot has read the site and summarized what's here — lists, libraries, pages.
This is grounded in the actual site content, not a generic description.

[pause]

[prompt: What kinds of lists does this site have?]

[wait]

Notice how Copilot can break down the inventory further. You can keep asking
follow-up questions in the same conversation.

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/site-overview.png]

[section: reset]

This demo is read-only — no content was created or modified.
Navigate back to the home page and close the chat pane to reset the view.

[navigate: https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]
